Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
readPackage(25.10)                                          readPackage(25.10)

Name
       readPackage  - Reads the package file dumped out by the System-in-Pack-
       age (SiP) layout in XML format and displays the package ball/finger lo-
       cation in the Innovus floorplan view

Syntax
       readPackage

       [-help]

       <packageFile>

       Reads the package file dumped out by the System-in-Package (SiP) layout
       in XML format and displays the package ball/finger location in the  In-
       novus  floorplan  view. The command also displays the flight lines from
       the IO pads to fingers for a wire-bond design or from bumps to  package
       balls for a flip chip design.

       The  package  overlay  schema  dumped  out by SiP includes bond finger,
       package balls, and many other package objects. readPackage displays all
       the package objects for a  wire-bond  or  flip  chip  design,  such  as
       BGA_BALL,  BOND_FINGER, BONDWIRE and ROUTE, in the Innovus main window.
       The exact information displayed depends on  the  package  overlay  file
       dumped  out by SiP. You can turn on or turn off the display of specific
       package objects using the Custom tab of the Color Preferences  form  in
       Innovus. You can view attributes of a selected package object using At-
       tribute Editor.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  out the command usage that includes type and default in-
              formation for each readPackage parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man readPackage

       <packageFile>
              Specifies the name of the package file.

Related Information
